The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques to analyze unstructured textual data in annual reports for predicting corporate distress. This falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by the arXiv categories cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which is a popular technique in the field of artificial intelligence (AI), covered by the cs.AI category. Additionally, the paper deals with the prediction of corporate distress, which is related to the field of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it involves identifying potential threats to the financial stability of a company. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of textual data, which is also related to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR).
